# 🍜 Week 1 - Danny's Diner

This folder contains my solution to **Week 1: Danny’s Diner** from the [8-Week SQL Challenge](https://8weeksqlchallenge.com/case-study-1/).

## 📊 Case Study Summary

Danny owns a restaurant and wants to better understand customer preferences and behaviors. The challenge focuses on analyzing customer visit patterns, menu choices, and loyalty.

## 📄 Files

- `week1-queries.sql` — SQL solutions to all 10 questions.

## ✅ Skills Used

- Basic SQL SELECTs
- JOINs and filtering
- Aggregation (`COUNT`, `MAX`, `MIN`)
- Subqueries
- Date-based filtering

## 🔍 Key Insights

- Customers frequently order ramen.
- C02 (customer ID 2) is the most loyal, with the highest number of visits.
- Each customer’s first item and overall frequency patterns were identified.

## 📌 Notes

I used MySQL for this challenge. Queries are written to be readable and modular.
